\label{eq:var_q}
\end{eqnarray}
We note that $\mathscr{V}_t$ is the conditional variance of the observable $q$.

The filter equation for the observable $q$ is of Kalman-Bucy form. In
such cases, if the initial state implies a Gaussian distribution for $q$,
